= ABOUT

Ruby script to send emails through Postmark.

This is a simple Ruby script that does not depend on any gems or additional libraries. 
Easy to use and useful when you need to send emails from some server that doesn't have SMTP configured.

= USAGE

The usage is similar to sendmail's console command:

cat /var/log/server.log | postmail wildbit.com 09304fb12ca7bcb8e01a09a7a5bdcd7fa8d8f598 admin@wildbit.com sdmitry@gmail.com "Your server is down!"

= INSTALLATION

* Copy to /usr/bin or /usr/local/bin and set executable flag. 
* Don't forget to enable SMTP API in your Postmark account.